{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"You are a high-ranking\nmilitary service member"},{"time":4280,"text":"deployed to Afghanistan."},{"time":7840,"text":"You are responsible for the lives"},{"time":10400,"text":"of hundreds of men and women,"},{"time":12560,"text":"and your base is under attack."},{"time":15855,"text":"Incoming mortar rounds\nare exploding all around you."},{"time":20080,"text":"Struggling to see\nthrough the dust and the smoke,"},{"time":23400,"text":"you do your best to assist the wounded"},{"time":26040,"text":"and then crawl to a nearby bunker."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29309,"text":"Conscious but dazed by the blasts,"},{"time":32040,"text":"you lay on your side and attempt\nto process what has just happened."},{"time":37800,"text":"As you regain your vision,"},{"time":40160,"text":"you see a bloody face"},{"time":42440,"text":"staring back at you."},{"time":45480,"text":"The image is terrifying,"},{"time":48360,"text":"but you quickly come to understand"},{"time":50880,"text":"it's not real."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54240,"text":"This vision continues to visit you\nmultiple times a day and in your sleep."},{"time":59360,"text":"You choose not to tell anyone\nfor fear of losing your job"},{"time":62720,"text":"or being seen as weak."},{"time":66080,"text":"You give the vision a name,"},{"time":68000,"text":"Bloody Face in Bunker,"},{"time":70120,"text":"and call it BFIB for short."},{"time":73800,"text":"You keep BFIB locked away in your mind,"},{"time":77040,"text":"secretly haunting you,"},{"time":78840,"text":"for the next seven years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83680,"text":"Now close your eyes."},{"time":87160,"text":"Can you see BFIB?"},{"time":91840,"text":"If you can, you're beginning\nto see the face"},{"time":94400,"text":"of the invisible wounds of war,"},{"time":96840,"text":"commonly known\nas post-traumatic stress disorder"},{"time":99720,"text":"and traumatic brain injury."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102320,"text":"While I can't say I have\npost-traumatic stress disorder,"},{"time":105040,"text":"I've never been a stranger to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107800,"text":"When I was a little girl, I would visit\nmy grandparents every summer."},{"time":112680,"text":"It was my grandfather"},{"time":114000,"text":"who introduced me to the effects\nof combat on the psyche."},{"time":118640,"text":"While my grandfather was serving\nas a Marine in the Korean War,"},{"time":122360,"text":"a bullet pierced his neck\nand rendered him unable to cry out."},{"time":127280,"text":"He watched as a corpsman passed him over,"},{"time":129919,"text":"declaring him a goner,"},{"time":131480,"text":"and then leaving him to die."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134960,"text":"Years later, after his\nphysical wounds had healed"},{"time":137600,"text":"and he'd returned home,"},{"time":139240,"text":"he rarely spoke of his\nexperiences in waking life."},{"time":143880,"text":"But at night I would hear him\nshouting obscenities"},{"time":146560,"text":"from his room down the hall."},{"time":149080,"text":"And during the day I would announce myself\nas I entered the room,"},{"time":152680,"text":"careful not to startle or agitate him."},{"time":156880,"text":"He lived out the remainder of his days"},{"time":159440,"text":"isolated and tight-lipped,"},{"time":161560,"text":"never finding a way to express himself,"},{"time":164360,"text":"and I didn't yet\nhave the tools to guide him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169560,"text":"I wouldn't have a name\nfor my grandfather's condition"},{"time":172120,"text":"until I was in my 20s."},{"time":174880,"text":"Seeking a graduate degree in art therapy,"},{"time":177960,"text":"I naturally gravitated\ntowards the study of trauma."},{"time":182480,"text":"And while sitting in class learning\nabout post-traumatic stress disorder,"},{"time":185960,"text":"or PTSD for short,"},{"time":188320,"text":"my mission to help service members\nwho suffered like my grandfather"},{"time":192040,"text":"began to take form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195160,"text":"We've had various names\nfor post-traumatic stress"},{"time":197840,"text":"throughout the history of war:"},{"time":200480,"text":"homesickness,"},{"time":202400,"text":"soldier's heart,"},{"time":204600,"text":"shell shock,"},{"time":206640,"text":"thousand-yard stare, for instance."},{"time":209760,"text":"And while I was pursuing my degree,\na new war was raging,"},{"time":213440,"text":"and thanks to modern body armor\nand military vehicles,"},{"time":216680,"text":"service members were surviving\nblast injuries they wouldn't have before."},{"time":221800,"text":"But the invisible wounds\nwere reaching new levels,"},{"time":224640,"text":"and this pushed military doctors\nand researchers"},{"time":227920,"text":"to try and truly understand the effects\nthat traumatic brain injury, or TBI,"},{"time":233240,"text":"and PTSD have on the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236760,"text":"Due to advances\nin technology and neuroimaging,"},{"time":240160,"text":"we now know there's\nan actual shutdown in the Broca's,"},{"time":243320,"text":"or the speech-language area of the brain,\nafter an individual experiences trauma."},{"time":249400,"text":"This physiological change,"},{"time":251240,"text":"or speechless terror as it's often called,"},{"time":254360,"text":"coupled with mental health stigma,"},{"time":256680,"text":"the fear of being judged"},{"time":258440,"text":"or misunderstood,"},{"time":259920,"text":"possibly even removed\nfrom their current duties,"},{"time":262600,"text":"has led to the invisible struggles\nof our servicemen and women."},{"time":267840,"text":"Generation after generation of veterans"},{"time":271440,"text":"have chosen not to talk\nabout their experiences,"},{"time":274720,"text":"and suffer in solitude."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278960,"text":"I had my work cut out for me\nwhen I got my first job"},{"time":281920,"text":"as an art therapist at the nation's\nlargest military medical center,"},{"time":285600,"text":"Walter Reed."},{"time":287480,"text":"After working for a few years\non a locked-in patient psychiatric unit,"},{"time":291400,"text":"I eventually transferred to the National\nIntrepid Center of Excellence, NICoE,"},{"time":296320,"text":"which leads TBI care\nfor active duty service members."},{"time":300760,"text":"Now, I believed in art therapy,"},{"time":302960,"text":"but I was going to have\nto convince service members,"},{"time":306000,"text":"big, tough, strong, manly military men,"},{"time":309760,"text":"and some women too,"},{"time":311520,"text":"to give art-making as\na psychotherapeutic intervention a try."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316680,"text":"The results have been\nnothing short of spectacular."},{"time":322000,"text":"Vivid, symbolic artwork"},{"time":324400,"text":"is being created\nby our servicemen and women,"},{"time":327400,"text":"and every work of art tells a story."},{"time":331400,"text":"We've observed that the process\nof art therapy bypasses"},{"time":334160,"text":"the speech-language issue with the brain."},{"time":337040,"text":"Art-making accesses the same sensory\nareas of the brain that encode trauma."},{"time":342480,"text":"Service members can use the art-making\nto work through their experiences"},{"time":345960,"text":"in a nonthreatening way."},{"time":348280,"text":"They can then apply words\nto their physical creations,"},{"time":351200,"text":"reintegrating the left\nand the right hemispheres of the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356520,"text":"Now, we've seen this can work\nwith all forms of art --"},{"time":360120,"text":"drawing, painting, collage --"},{"time":363400,"text":"but what seems to have the most impact"},{"time":366680,"text":"is mask-making."},{"time":369120,"text":"Finally, these invisible wounds\ndon't just have a name,"},{"time":373800,"text":"they have a face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377280,"text":"And when service members\ncreate these masks,"},{"time":379480,"text":"it allows them to come to grips,\nliterally, with their trauma."},{"time":383680,"text":"And it's amazing\nhow often that enables them"},{"time":386000,"text":"to break through the trauma\nand start to heal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390800,"text":"Remember BFIB?"},{"time":394320,"text":"That was a real experience\nfor one of my patients,"},{"time":397360,"text":"and when he created his mask,"},{"time":398840,"text":"he was able to let go\nof that haunting image."},{"time":402800,"text":"Initially, it was a daunting process\nfor the service member,"},{"time":405960,"text":"but eventually he began\nto think of BFIB as the mask,"},{"time":408960,"text":"not his internal wound,"},{"time":410640,"text":"and he would go to leave each session,"},{"time":412520,"text":"he would hand me the mask,\nand say, \"Melissa, take care of him.\""},{"time":416440,"text":"Eventually, we placed BFIB in a box\nto further contain him,"},{"time":420760,"text":"and when the service member\nwent to leave the NICoE,"},{"time":423240,"text":"he chose to leave BFIB behind."},{"time":426240,"text":"A year later, he had only seen BFIB twice,"},{"time":428920,"text":"and both times BFIB was smiling"},{"time":430640,"text":"and the service member\ndidn't feel anxious."},{"time":434000,"text":"Now, whenever that service member\nis haunted by some traumatic memory,"},{"time":437360,"text":"he continues to paint."},{"time":440000,"text":"Every time he paints\nthese disturbing images,"},{"time":442640,"text":"he sees them less or not at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"Philosophers have told us\nfor thousands of years"},{"time":450720,"text":"that the power to create"},{"time":452000,"text":"is very closely linked\nto the power to destroy."},{"time":455720,"text":"Now science is showing us\nthat the part of the brain"},{"time":458200,"text":"that registers a traumatic wound"},{"time":460240,"text":"can be the part of the brain\nwhere healing happens too."},{"time":463800,"text":"And art therapy is showing us\nhow to make that connection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468320,"text":"We asked one of our service members"},{"time":470240,"text":"to describe how mask-making\nimpacted his treatment,"},{"time":473600,"text":"and this is what he had to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475760,"text":"(Video) Service Member:\nYou sort of just zone out into the mask."},{"time":478840,"text":"You zone out into the drawing,"},{"time":480320,"text":"and for me, it just released the block,"},{"time":484920,"text":"so I was able to do it."},{"time":487600,"text":"And then when I looked at it\nafter two days, I was like,"},{"time":491240,"text":"\"Holy crap, here's the picture,\nhere's the key, here's the puzzle,\""},{"time":494600,"text":"and then from there it just soared."},{"time":496680,"text":"I mean, from there\nmy treatment just when out of sight,"},{"time":500160,"text":"because they were like,\nKurt, explain this, explain this."},{"time":502880,"text":"And for the first time in 23 years,"},{"time":504720,"text":"I could actually talk about stuff\nopenly to, like, anybody."},{"time":507640,"text":"I could talk to you about it\nright now if I wanted to,"},{"time":510760,"text":"because it unlocked it."},{"time":513440,"text":"It's just amazing."},{"time":514720,"text":"And it allowed me to put 23 years of PTSD"},{"time":520280,"text":"and TBI stuff together in one place"},{"time":526280,"text":"that has never happened before."},{"time":530040,"text":"Sorry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531920,"text":"Melissa Walker: Over the past five years,"},{"time":533920,"text":"we've had over 1,000 masks made."},{"time":537760,"text":"It's pretty amazing, isn't it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":540640,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541880,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":547440,"text":"I wish I could have shared\nthis process with my grandfather,"},{"time":551800,"text":"but I know that he would be thrilled"},{"time":555040,"text":"that we are finding ways"},{"time":556720,"text":"to help today's and tomorrow's\nservice members heal,"},{"time":561400,"text":"and finding the resources within them"},{"time":564640,"text":"that they can call upon"},{"time":566360,"text":"to heal themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569680,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570920,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}